<pre class="brush: sql; toolbar: false">
           foo = {
           		'foo' : {
                       'hello' : 'Hello',
                       'world' : 'World'
                   	    }
                 }
           zero = {'zero' : null}
           mycond = select * from foo
           empty = select * from zero
           if(empty || !!mycond)
            {
                a = select * from foo
            }
           else
            {
                b = select * from bar
            }
           return "{a}" || "{b}"
</pre>
<p>This script returns "foo" after conditional execution</p>

<p>The else logic is optional. The statement works without any else logic as well.</p>

<p>The script can handle different levels of nestings within any if block or else block.</p>

